@page "/blog/investing-guide-nigeria"
@using SmartBudget.Components.Pages.Blog
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@inherits BlogPostBase

<PageTitle>SmartBudget - Beginner's Guide to Investing in Nigeria</PageTitle>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/blog.css" />

<div class="blog-post-page">
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <div class="breadcrumb-container">
            <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house-door"></i> Home</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/blog">Blog</a></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><i class="bi bi-chevron-right"></i></li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">Investing Guide</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
        </div>

        <article class="blog-post">
            <div class="post-header">
                <span class="post-category-badge">Investing</span>
                <h1>Beginner's Guide to Investing in Nigeria</h1>
                <div class="post-meta">
                    <span><i class="bi bi-person-circle"></i> SmartBudget Team</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-calendar3"></i> @CurrentDate</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-clock"></i> 8 min read</span>
                    <span><i class="bi bi-file-text"></i> Beginner</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="post-body-content">
                <p>Investing is the key to building long-term wealth. This comprehensive guide covers everything you need to know about investing in Nigeria in @CurrentYear.</p>

                <h2>Why Invest?</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Beat inflation:</strong> Grow your money faster than the cost of living</li>
                    <li><strong>Build wealth:</strong> Create long-term financial security</li>
                    <li><strong>Passive income:</strong> Earn money while you sleep</li>
                    <li><strong>Financial freedom:</strong> Achieve your goals faster</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Investment Options in Nigeria</h2>
                
                <h3>1. Nigerian Stocks (Equities)</h3>
                <p>Buy shares in companies listed on the Nigerian Exchange (NGX).</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Pros:</strong> High growth potential, dividends</li>
                    <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Volatile, requires research</li>
                    <li><strong>Minimum:</strong> ₦5,000 - ₦10,000</li>
                    <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Stockbrokers (e.g., Cordros, FBNQuest)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>2. Treasury Bills</h3>
                <p>Short-term government securities with low risk.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Very safe, good for short-term</li>
                    <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Low returns compared to stocks</li>
                    <li><strong>Minimum:</strong> ₦100,000</li>
                    <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Primary Dealer Market</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>3. Mutual Funds</h3>
                <p>Professional managed investment pools.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Diversification, professional management</li>
                    <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Management fees</li>
                    <li><strong>Minimum:</strong> ₦5,000 - ₦10,000</li>
                    <li><strong>Platforms:</strong> Stanbic IBTC, ARM, FBN</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>4. Real Estate</h3>
                <p>Property investment for rental income or capital appreciation.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Tangible asset, rental income</li>
                    <li><strong>Cons:</strong> High capital requirement</li>
                    <li><strong>Minimum:</strong> ₦1,000,000+</li>
                    <li><strong>Platforms:</strong> Real estate companies, REITs</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>5. REITs (Real Estate Investment Trusts)</h3>
                <p>Invest in real estate without buying property directly.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Low minimum, regular income</li>
                    <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Market volatility</li>
                    <li><strong>Minimum:</strong> ₦10,000</li>
                    <li><strong>Platform:</strong> Nigerian Stock Exchange</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Comparison of Investment Options</h2>
                <div class="table-wrapper">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Investment Type</th>
                                <th>Risk Level</th>
                                <th>Minimum (₦)</th>
                                <th>Liquidity</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Stocks</td>
                                <td>High</td>
                                <td>5,000 - 10,000</td>
                                <td>High</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Treasury Bills</td>
                                <td>Low</td>
                                <td>100,000</td>
                                <td>Medium</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Mutual Funds</td>
                                <td>Medium</td>
                                <td>5,000 - 10,000</td>
                                <td>High</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Real Estate</td>
                                <td>Medium</td>
                                <td>1,000,000+</td>
                                <td>Low</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>REITs</td>
                                <td>Medium</td>
                                <td>10,000</td>
                                <td>High</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h2>How to Start Investing</h2>
                <h3>Step 1: Set Your Investment Goals</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Short-term (1-3 years): Emergency fund, vacation</li>
                    <li>Medium-term (3-5 years): House down payment, education</li>
                    <li>Long-term (5+ years): Retirement, children's future</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Step 2: Choose Your Investment Platform</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Stockbroker account for stocks</li>
                    <li>Investment platform for mutual funds</li>
                    <li>Real estate platforms for property investments</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Step 3: Start Small</h3>
                <p>You don't need millions to start. Begin with whatever you can afford.</p>

                <h3>Step 4: Diversify</h3>
                <p>Don't put all your money in one investment. Spread it across different asset classes.</p>

                <h3>Step 5: Stay Informed</h3>
                <p>Keep learning about investing. Read financial news and analysis regularly.</p>

                <h2>Common Investment Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Not doing enough research before investing</li>
                    <li>Following the crowd without analysis</li>
                    <li>Investing money you can't afford to lose</li>
                    <li>Not diversifying your portfolio</li>
                    <li>Panic selling during market downturns</li>
                    <li>Not considering inflation and fees</li>
                    <li>Chasing quick returns without understanding the risks</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Investment Tips for Nigerians</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Start with mutual funds</strong> if you're a beginner</li>
                    <li><strong>Consider dollar-denominated investments</strong> to hedge against currency risk</li>
                    <li><strong>Use dollar-cost averaging</strong> to reduce market timing risk</li>
                    <li><strong>Keep some investments in liquid assets</strong> for emergencies</li>
                    <li><strong>Review your portfolio quarterly</strong> and rebalance as needed</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="post-cta">
                    <h3>Start Your Investment Journey</h3>
                    <p>Track your investments with SmartBudget.</p>
                    <a href="/Account/Register" class="btn-cta">Get Started Free →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</div>


@code {
    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        PageName = "blog-post";
        await base.OnInitializedAsync();
    }
}